==English==

===Etymology===
From '''[[acro-]]''' "sharp, high" + '''[[-onym]]''' "name", modelled after '''[[homonym]]''' and '''[[synonym]]'''.  From {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἄκρος]]}}''' (akros) "extremity" and '''{{polytonic|[[ὄνομα]]}}''' "name".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈæk.ɹə.nɪm/}}, {{SAMPA|/"{k.r\@.nIm/}}
*{{audio|en-uk-acronym.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[abbreviation]] formed by (usually initial) [[letters]] taken from a word or series of words, and which is itself pronounced as a word.
# Any abbreviation so formed, regardless of pronunciation.

